			<div class="content" id="post-content-4723049">
									

<p><sup>Votes don't help the author, so I've vowed to always leave a comment with mine, at the very least whenever I rate an article negatively. If you feel the same, help out by leaving critique with more of your votes. Comment follows:</sup></p>
<p>As a set of achievements, I do not get a good vibe from these. I explain my thoughts in more detail on the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-13455611/scp-achievement-badges#post-4723048">other achievements page</a>. Primarily I don't like how the achievements reward ratings, which are not a good measure of a page's quality or of an author's worth.</p>
<p>It makes far more sense to me to reward good, ongoing contributions to the site, like pages authored in a canon.</p>
<p>A lot of the achievements on this page specifically are just not good at all. &quot;<em>Holding the highest number of reviewers-spotlight articles in the site.</em>&quot; can only be achieved by one person. &quot;<em>Author of at least 10 [pages that] are downvoted by the same member.</em>&quot; encourages malicious downvoting. A lot of the achievements simply encourage repetition of tropes and clichés. There's also this weird mix of incredibly specific achievements and incredibly generic ones.</p>
<p>As an artwork page, the icons are actually pretty good. So it's a novote from me overall.</p>

							</div>

								
