			<div class="content" id="post-content-4723220">
									

<p>Seconding this. Ratings, especially in regards to tales and GoI formats, simply aren’t a very good attribute to an article’s merit.</p>
<p>Most tales don’t get nearly the same clicks as most SCP articles, so IMO a “good tale rating” is on average closer to +40. Honestly, it just seems a bit like snubbing people who write non-scp articles by accident because tales can typically languish at +15 despite having quality ideas.</p>
<p>That’s just my take, though. Not trying to seem salty or anything. I love the art here!</p>

